	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000457_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><hi rend="underline">To <persName>Janet <choice><sic>Livingston</sic><corr>Livingstone</corr></choice></persName></hi></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space unit="chars" extent="2"/>My Dear Sister</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><space unit="words" extent="3"/>I send you these lines which 
<lb/>I received as a <hi rend="underline">reliquaire</hi> from my friend <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Banff</persName>. 
<lb/>Accept them as a token of my unabated affection, and 
<lb/>sincere wish that the <orgName>Christian's</orgName> exalted hope may 
<lb/>be your portion through Life; and though we may not 
<lb/>meet again in Time, that you and all my beloved 
<lb/>relatives and friends, may meet where separation 
<lb/>and sorrow are unknown, To sing the praises of 
<lb/>our dear Redeeemer, who Loved &amp; gave himself for us. </p>
<lb/><p><space unit="words" extent="8"/>Your Affectionate Brother</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space unit="chars" extent="3"/><hi rend="underline"><placeName><settlement type="town">Ongar</settlement></placeName>, <placeName><region>Essex</region></placeName></hi>, Oct<hi rend="sup">r</hi> 3 <hi rend="sup">d</hi>/58 </p>
<lb/><p><space unit="words" extent="9"/><hi rend="underline"><persName>David <choice><sic>Livingston</sic><corr>Livingstone</corr></choice></persName></hi></p>	
		
</div>
